<body>
  <header>
    <div class="pill">Privacy Policy</div>
    <h1>GirlSpace</h1>
    <div class="sub">Effective date: 12 November 2025 • Last updated: 12 November 2025</div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <p>GirlSpace (“<strong>App</strong>”) is provided by <strong>QTI Labs Pvt. Ltd.</strong> (“<strong>we</strong>”, “<strong>us</strong>”, “<strong>our</strong>”). This policy explains what data we collect, why we collect it, and how you can control it.</p>

    <h2>1. What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account data</strong> via sign-in providers:
        <ul>
          <li><em>Google Sign-In</em>: name, email, profile photo, Google UID.</li>
          <li><em>Facebook Login</em>: name, email (if granted), profile photo, Facebook UID.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li><strong>App usage & content</strong>: profile information you add (bio, display name), media you upload (images/videos), preferences, timestamps.</li>
      <li><strong>Device & diagnostics</strong>: basic device info, OS version, in-app events, and crash logs (if enabled) to improve reliability.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How we use data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Authenticate you and keep your account secure.</li>
      <li>Provide core features (profiles, social actions, storage of your content).</li>
      <li>Moderate content and prevent abuse/spam.</li>
      <li>Improve performance, troubleshoot issues, and develop new features.</li>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Legal bases</h2>
    <p>We process data based on your consent (e.g., connecting Google/Facebook), contract (to provide the App), and legitimate interests (security, moderation, improvement).</p>

    <h2>4. Where data is stored</h2>
    <p>We use <strong>Google Firebase</strong> services:
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Firebase Auth</strong> for login.</li>
        <li><strong>Cloud Firestore</strong> for app data and profiles.</li>
        <li><strong>Firebase Storage</strong> for media uploads.</li>
      </ul>
      Data may be processed in data centers outside your country, subject to adequate safeguards.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Third-party services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google</strong> (Firebase, Google Sign-In)</li>
      <li><strong>Meta</strong> (Facebook Login)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We currently do <strong>not</strong> serve ads. If this changes, this policy will be updated before ads go live.</p>

    <h2>6. Data sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not sell personal data. We share only as needed to operate the App, comply with the law, protect users, or in a business transfer (e.g., merger), with appropriate safeguards.</p>

    <h2>7. Data retention & deletion</h2>
    <p>We retain data while your account is active. You can request deletion at any time (see “Your rights”). Backups may persist for a limited period.</p>

    <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Access, correct, or delete your data.</li>
      <li>Export a copy of your data (on request).</li>
      <li>Withdraw consents you previously granted.</li>
      <li>Contact us to raise a concern or complaint.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>9. Security</h2>
    <p>We use technical and organizational safeguards (authentication, access control, encryption in transit) but no method is 100% secure.</p>

    <h2>10. Children</h2>
    <p>The App is not intended for children under 13. If we learn we’ve collected data from a child under applicable age limits, we will delete it.</p>

    <h2>11. International users</h2>
    <p>By using the App, you understand your information may be transferred and processed outside your country in accordance with this policy.</p>

    <h2>12. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy. The “Last updated” date will change, and material changes will be communicated in-app or on this page.</p>

    <h2>13. Contact</h2>
    <p>QTI Labs Pvt. Ltd.<br/>
       Email: <a href="mailto:support@qtilabs.com">support@qtilabs.com</a><br/>
       Address: Hyderabad, Telangana, India
    </p>
  </main>

